CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1945, pg. 9 reads: "Big Doings - It was a really gay time at the home of Miss Ethel Lewis Tuesday night at 717 Finland Street, where she celebrated her birthday with a swanky party. As it turned out, it was a double celebration as her birthdate fell on V-E Day. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of men and women gathered around Ethel Lewis holding flowers, posed in her home for birthday party
